deseronto transit provides a public transportation service in rural hastings county, ontario and prince edward county, ontario. although operated by the municipal government of deseronto, ontario, the small system is mostly intercity in nature. most service is operated with 15 passenger vans, as opposed to buses. two routes are offered. one connects deseronto with greater napanee in the east and the city of belleville; this route runs 4 times per weekday, with a single trip on saturday that requires advanced reservations. the other line runs from picton and bloomfield to deseronto, with 4 trips per weekday and a single sunday trip.